      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Very little between the top two. We'll lean the way of SASS APPEAL (2) who has won three on the bounce, leading throughout to win the Desirable Stakes here last time out. She got an easy time there with Ole Dancer ridden cold behind her, but she'll get favours again and can take plenty of catching. SALTY PEARL (1) is the clear danger. She bumped into Sheza Alibi last time in the Angus Armanasco but beat the rest and will be peaking now. LATHLAIN (7) was utterly dominant in a BM66 fresh at $1.45 having shown stakes level ability last time in work. She can take that next step. PILLOW FIGHT (5) is a handy filly down from Sydney who can run well.",
